30/03/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- The excellent level of US-Romanian co-operation was reaffirmed at a meeting between US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice and Romanian Foreign Minister Mihai-Razvan Ungureanu in Washington on Wednesday (29 March), according to a press release issued on Thursday in Bucharest. The talks focused mostly on issues related to prospects for stability and security in the Balkans and the Black Sea region. Rice and Ungureanu also confirmed their countries' mutual interest in the fast ratification and implementation of the bilateral agreement establishing US military bases on Romanian territory. (Nine o'clock - 30/03/06; Rompres - 29/03/06)
